/docs#keep-going","content":"Add some labels:"},"104":{"id":"/docs-14","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#keep-going","content":"Place it on the top instead:"},"105":{"id":"/docs-15","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-next","content":"<Card title=\"Explore all the options\" href=\"/docs/charts/barchart\" />"},"106":{"id":"/docs-16","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-next","content":"<Card title=\"Check out a ton of example usage\" href=\"/docs/examples\" />"},"107":{"id":"/docs-17","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-next","content":"<Card title=\"Open an Issue\" href=\"#\" />"},"108":{"id":"/docs-18","page_id":"/docs","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs#what-next","content":"<Card title=\"Explode!\" href=\"#\" />"},"109":{"id":"/docs/roadmap","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"page","content":"Roadmap","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Introduction"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap"},"110":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-0","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap","content":"Where're things heading?"},"111":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-1","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#currently-working-on","content":"Currently Working On"},"112":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-2","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#svelte-package","content":"Svelte Package"},"113":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-3","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"3D Charts"},"114":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-4","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#docs-updates","content":"Docs Updates"},"115":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-5","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#planned-features","content":"Planned Features"},"116":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-6","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#legend-creation-util","content":"Legend Creation Util"},"117":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-7","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#consistent-styling","content":"Consistent Styling"},"118":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-8","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#accessibility","content":"Accessibility"},"119":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-9","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#tabled-for-now","content":"Tabled For Now"},"120":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-10","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#ascii--text-output","content":"ASCII / Text Output"},"121":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-11","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/roadmap#additional-chart-options","content":"Additional Chart Options"},"122":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-12","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap","content":"This is not set in stone, nor is there a definitive timeline for when or if pieces of what's here will arrive. But rather this should serve as 'what to expect' for the library."},"123":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-13","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap","content":"If you want a deeper dive on the old roadmap & insight on things in general, check out my train of thought here the 6/16/2026 entry in particular."},"124":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-14","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#currently-working-on","content":"This is the answer to \"What's up next?\""},"125":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-15","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#svelte-package","content":"Will live under `@jgmc/svelte`!"},"126":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-16","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"That's right I'm bringing in the third dimension. This isn't just \"3D-looking\" versions what I already have, but I plan to work on WebGPU powered 3D visualizations."},"127":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-17","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"The first three are slated to be:"},"128":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-18","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"Volumetric Visualization"},"129":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-19","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"3D Bivariate / Mesh Surface Plot"},"130":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-20","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#3d-charts","content":"Lidar / 3D Point Clouds"},"131":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-21","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#docs-updates","content":"Many improvements to be made!"},"132":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-22","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#planned-features","content":"These are things I definitely am aiming to add likely sooner rather than later."},"133":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-23","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#legend-creation-util","content":"Would be a standalone function that takes some similar input to charts, and spits out a neat legend."},"134":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-24","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#consistent-styling","content":"While the current styling options are good, it would be annoying to redeclare them everywhere. An entire theming system feels overkill though."},"135":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-25","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#consistent-styling","content":"This may come down to better built-in classes & giving some optional CSS for easy consistent styling."},"136":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-26","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#consistent-styling","content":"Need to flesh out ideas for this more though."},"137":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-27","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#accessibility","content":"I'm unsure how much there is in terms of accessibility for SVG charts, but I'd like to add optional support for what's out there. Optional as not every chart is public facing or output size could matter."},"138":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-28","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#tabled-for-now","content":"Low impact and may have too big of a lift for it to be worthwhile."},"139":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-29","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#ascii--text-output","content":"While I really like this idea, it doesn't feel very compelling. There's only so much you can do with text in terminals, charts while cool may not be quite as effective in text-form."},"140":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-30","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#ascii--text-output","content":"I do want to do ASCII versions of charts at some point, but it's not a priority now."},"141":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-31","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#ascii--text-output","content":"Or maybe I'll cheat and use sixels... We'll see, tabled for now!"},"142":{"id":"/docs/roadmap-32","page_id":"/docs/roadmap","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/roadmap#additional-chart-options","content":"I'm open to adding more options for charts, but for now I think the current set of options are more than enough."},"143":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","type":"page","content":"Why JGMC?","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Introduction"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/why-jgmc"},"144":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-0","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc","content":"What's the point of this library?"},"145":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-1","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Motivation"},"146":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-2","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Chart \r\n/CHärt/> a sheet of information\r\nin the form of a table, graph, or diagram."},"147":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-3","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"It's no secret that there are already many, time-tested libraries & tools out there capable of making highly complex, beautiful charts & more - many offer a multitude of data visualization options."},"148":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-4","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Some of my favorites:"},"149":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-5","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Chart.js"},"150":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-6","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"a feature rich, modular library for crafting many types of charts with tons of options"},"151":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-7","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"d3.js"},"152":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-8","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"one of the most powerful data visualization options out there, going way beyond charts"},"153":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-9","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"ApexCharts.js"},"154":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-10","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"a nice and cohesive chart creation lib with everything you need to create a range of charts"},"155":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-11","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"I used this way back in the day where it was totally free - looks like they\r\nhave an enterprise paid license now, good for them!"},"156":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-12","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"I have fun making any sort of visuals, and a good visual can really say a lot! But you know what else I've really come to appreciate? Simplicity! And while not a library, I do find myself utilizing google sheets quite a bit, and I came across the `SPARKLINE` function."},"157":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-13","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"While I haven't had a ton of opportunities as of late to utilize it, I was impressed by how simple it could be to use, and how much it could add in terms of conveying information. Let's look at some examples."},"158":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-14","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Consider that you have the following dataset:"},"159":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-15","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Now if you wanted a sense of how the data was trending, or changing over those cells you need to read each one to get that sense, which is fine. But what if you had 30 different columns, or what if the exact values weren't important? Or you just want to speed up that process?"},"160":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-16","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Well this would help you glean that same information much quicker:"},"161":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-17","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"If you've used sheets before, you know making a chart is typically possible though not always the most cohesive experience. You highlight your data, go to \"insert\", choose \"chart\" then the type, and configure the various options. Which isn't terrible, it can also do more - but sometimes less is more."},"162":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-18","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"So that line graph though is within it's own cell, not floating on the sheet. And how does `SPARKLINE` come into play? Well, that's all it takes!"},"163":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-19","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Not a bar chart, but we can make it one with just a little bit of configuration:"},"164":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-20","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"Just by adding that second argument, `{\"charttype\",\"column\"}` it's a whole different visual! But that's not all it can do, there's a bunch more configuration options, and even a couple more chart types docs here! and that sort of \"effort in\" to \"value out\" is what I'm aiming for here."},"165":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-21","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"So why toomanycharts? Time! I hope to create something that saves developers time,I want a library that can make meaningful simple charts, with trivial effort required. I hope this library is something more of a useful tool for quick & simple chart creation, whether it be a small panel in an admin dashboard, a placeholder until there's time to create a better chart, or even a debugging tool."},"166":{"id":"/docs/why-jgmc-22","page_id":"/docs/why-jgmc","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/why-jgmc#motivation","content":"If you're curious of what's to come, check out the Roadmap page for what I'm thinking of what's to come."},"167":{"id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","page_id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","type":"page","content":"Charts Classes","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Usage","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/guides/chart-classes"},"168":{"id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes-0","page_id":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/guides/chart-classes","content":"A look at default classes given to charts and their various elements, as well as ho