adients","content":"Continuous gradients also work, though this makes it almost impossible to tell the segments apart. Though this can be mitigated with CSS!"},"316":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples-19","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples#gradients","content":"Of course that's not the only way of using CSS to differentiate the segments:"},"317":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples-20","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/barchartstacked-examples#animation","content":"To be filled in, though the idea would be the same as barcharts - except you'd need to stagger the animation & delay it so that they play in sequence per-segment. Unless you want each bar appearing at once then it's identical."},"318":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","type":"page","content":"Donutchart Examples","breadcrumbs":["The Lib","Usage","Vanilla Charts Examples"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples"},"319":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples-0","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","content":"A cup of coffee and a donut, anyone?"},"320":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples-1","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples#donutchart","content":"`donutchart`"},"321":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples-2","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"322":{"id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchart-examples-3","page_id":"/docs/vanilla-examples/donutchar